# dm-verity prototype configuration.
#
# Read by vhdbuilder/packer/dmverity-prototype/install.sh during the
# AgentBaker AzureLinux 3 Packer build. To disable the prototype, set both
# URLs to empty strings; install.sh becomes a hard no-op and the VHD is
# identical to a stock build.
#
# Variables:
#   DMVERITY_RPM_URL    Anonymous-access URL to the patched containerd2 RPM
#                       built from steamboat/local-vm-scripts/build-rpm.sh
#                       containing the snapshotter signature handler
#                       (containerd pkg/snapshotters/signatures.go). As of
#                       2.0.1-3003 the RPM also ships a systemd drop-in
#                       (/etc/systemd/system/containerd.service.d/dmverity-overlay.conf)
#                       that re-overlays /usr/share/containerd2/config.toml
#                       onto /etc/containerd/config.toml on every containerd
#                       start, so AKS CSE's bootstrap-time clobber doesn't
#                       defeat the dm-verity config. Earlier 2.0.1-3001
#                       shipped the config + kernel-modules-load.d entry +
#                       Requires: erofs-utils / veritysetup -- no out-of-band
#                       wiring needed here.
#                       2.0.1-3005 re-pinned the pod sandbox image to
#                       notarycontainerregistry.azurecr.io/oss/v2/kubernetes/pause:3.6
#                       AND flipped both enforcement gates on
#                       (dmverity_mode=on, require_signatures=true).
#                       2.0.1-3006 re-pinned the pod sandbox image again to
#                       notaryaksegistry.azurecr.io/oss/v2/kubernetes/pause:3.6.
#                       notaryaksegistry lives in the
#                       EdgeOS_Mariner_Platform_AKS_test sub -- same sub as
#                       the aks-rp e2e clusters -- so the kubelet MSI gets
#                       AcrPull on the registry automatically via AKS attach
#                       and we avoid cross-sub RBAC plumbing. All 17 Phase 2
#                       images (pause + tier-1 + tier-2 minus aks-node-ca-watcher)
#                       have been re-mirrored and re-signed in notaryaksegistry.
#                       2.0.1-3007 wires AppendSignatureHandlerWrapper into
#                       the OCI-layout import path (new ContentStoreFetcher
#                       in pkg/snapshotters + wrap in core/transfer/local/import.go).
#                       Without this, the dm-verity sig handler only ran on
#                       registry-pull paths, so CSE's pull_pod_infra_container_image
#                       (oras cp --recursive + ctr image import --digests)
#                       produced an unsigned image view to the erofs differ
#                       which then failed with "dm-verity signature required
#                       but not present on layer ..." even with the sig
#                       manifest already in the local content store.
#                       2.0.1-3012 ships
#                       /etc/containerd/certs.d/mcr.microsoft.com/hosts.toml
#                       directly in the RPM. The file transparently redirects
#                       every mcr.microsoft.com pull (manifests, blobs, AND
#                       OCI referrers) to notaryaksegistry.azurecr.io where
#                       the cncf.notary.dmverity.v1 sigs live. Replaces the
#                       earlier BYO-ACR (BootstrapProfile.ContainerRegistryID)
#                       experiment, which AKS RP 400-rejects on every
#                       default-VNET cluster ("BootstrapProfile Bring Your
#                       Own(BYO) container registry is only allowed when VNET
#                       is custom" -- ate Scenario_AzureLinux_Addon in build
#                       166214159). hosts.toml mirroring is purely node-local
#                       and works on any VNET shape -- including the default
#                       VNET that the bulk of e2e scenarios use. The aks-rp
#                       hardcode was reverted in commit 2b44928c0a77 on
#                       dadelan/dmverity-cse-vendor-v2. Auth on the mirror
#                       relies on notaryaksegistry anonymous-pull being
#                       enabled (it is; verified via /oauth2/token + manifest
#                       fetch + referrers API at HTTP 200 on 2026-05-31).
#                       2.2.0-4001 jumps to upstream containerd 2.2.0
#                       (immutable pin @cb15e731a) via a patch-based spec
#                       and fixes a snapshotter Info.Labels regression that
#                       broke pulls of images signed with full enterprise
#                       PKCS#7 envelopes. The previous label key
#                       containerd.io/snapshot/dmverity.layer-signature
#                       matched snapshots.FilterInheritedLabels' prefix and
#                       auto-promoted the base64 PKCS#7 sig into a boltdb
#                       snapshot label, which exceeded boltdb's 4096-byte
#                       per-label cap when the sig was an ESRP
#                       Pkcs7DetachedSign envelope (RSA-4096 leaf + 2
#                       intermediates + RFC3161 timestamp counter-sig =
#                       ~5.7 KiB). Pull failed with InvalidArgument before
#                       Apply ever ran. The key prefix is renamed to
#                       containerd.io/dmverity/ which is NOT auto-promoted;
#                       the sidecar-file flow into veritysetup is unchanged.
#                       Validated end-to-end on dadelan-notary-test node 0
#                       against an ESRP CP-500049-signed pause:3.6.
#                       2.2.4-6000.verity moves containerd2 into the
#                       azurelinux@dadelan/kernel-update buddy-build set
#                       alongside the kernel (Release: 6000.verity%{?dist}
#                       in azurelinux/SPECS/containerd2/containerd2.spec).
#                       Validated end-to-end against ESRP-signed
#                       notaryaksegistry.azurecr.io/esrp-dev/azurelinux/distroless/minimal:3.0
#                       on dadelan-notary-test vmss000002 (snap 175,
#                       runtime rootHash 9def6c40... bit-equal to the
#                       signed rootHash) 2026-06-02 after fixing the ESRP
#                       per-layer UUID derivation in
#                       CBL-Mariner-Pipelines/pipelines/build-variants/
#                       templates/sign-dmverity-layers-stage.yaml.
#
#                       LEFT EMPTY INTENTIONALLY starting 2.2.4-6000.verity:
#                       the patched containerd2 RPM is delivered to the
#                       Packer build VM via the same buddy-build channel
#                       that ships the patched kernel
#                       (`proprietaryRpmBuddyBuildId` parameter on the
#                       buildAzureLinuxV3gen2 job, set in the ADO UI when
#                       the VHD build is queued). The pipeline downloads
#                       buddy-build artifacts and tdnf-installs them by
#                       file path BEFORE this install.sh runs. Pulling
#                       containerd2 from kataccstorage here is therefore
#                       redundant AND brittle (kataccstorage container
#                       public-access flag has to be enabled mid-build
#                       window or curl returns 409, observed on build
#                       1129685). install.sh now gates the containerd2
#                       RPM install on this URL being non-empty, the same
#                       way it gates the kernel RPM install.
#
#                       To re-enable URL-based containerd2 install (e.g.
#                       for a prototype path that does not use the
#                       buddy-build channel), populate this URL + SHA256.
#                       install.sh uses --disablerepo='preview-repo' +
#                       full-path install so the buddy-build install (if
#                       also present) is a NVR-equal idempotent no-op.
#   DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_URL
#                       Anonymous-access URL to the patched Azure Linux 3
#                       kernel RPM (azurelinux@dadelan/kernel-update,
#                       Release: 99.osguard1%{?dist}). Bakes the OS Guard CA
#                       into CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRUSTED_KEYS so dm-verity layer
#                       signatures are verified out of .builtin_trusted_keys
#                       at boot without runtime keyctl enrollment.
#
#                       LEFT EMPTY INTENTIONALLY: the patched kernel RPM is
#                       delivered to the Packer build VM via the
#                       mariner-aks-pipelines buddy-build channel
#                       (`proprietaryRpmBuddyBuildId` parameter on the
#                       buildAzureLinuxV3gen2 job, set in the ADO UI when
#                       the VHD build is queued). The pipeline downloads
#                       the kernel RPM from the buddy-build artifacts and
#                       tdnf-installs it by file path multiple times during
#                       standard install-dependencies.sh execution -- BEFORE
#                       this install.sh runs. Re-downloading it from
#                       kataccstorage here is redundant AND brittle (the
#                       kataccstorage container public-access flag has to
#                       be enabled mid-build window or curl returns 409,
#                       observed on build 1129685). Setting this URL empty
#                       short-circuits the redundant download at
#                       install.sh:102.
#
#                       To re-enable URL-based kernel install (e.g. for a
#                       prototype path that does not use the buddy-build
#                       channel), populate this URL + SHA256. install.sh
#                       still uses --disablerepo='preview-repo' + full-path
#                       install so the buddy-build install (if also present)
#                       is a NVR-equal idempotent no-op.
#   DMVERITY_CERT_URL   Anonymous-access URL to the PEM-encoded OS Guard
#                       signer CA. With the patched kernel this file is only
#                       useful for userspace verifiers (e.g. `notation verify`)
#                       and as a fallback for non-osguard kernels via the
#                       aks-dmverity-keyring.service unit.
#   DMVERITY_RPM_SHA256
#   DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_SHA256
#   DMVERITY_CERT_SHA256
#                       Optional integrity pins; verified after download.
#
# WARNING: kataccstorage public access must be enabled before the VHD
# build runs and disabled afterward. See ../README.md for the
# `az storage account update --allow-blob-public-access true|false` toggle.
DMVERITY_RPM_URL=
DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_URL=
DMVERITY_CERT_URL=https://kataccstorage.blob.core.windows.net/aks-rpms/osguard-signer-ca.pem
DMVERITY_RPM_SHA256=
DMVERITY_KERNEL_RPM_SHA256=
DMVERITY_CERT_SHA256=d33ea66794030396aca27e039715dbab4e15ccf5530fdf431f0ed7d05639afaa
